"about.app.content" = "This app is not the official app of the Rudolstadt Festival. It was developed unpaid as a hobby project, hoping to provide a more convenient user experience than the official app.

The app is up-to-date for the 2026 festival.

The app does not include third-party analytics, advertising SDKs, or tracking. Your festival profile data is stored on your device and can sync through Apple's iCloud service across your devices. If you choose to share your profile, invited friends can see your shared badge, saved events, and artist ratings. Artist notes stay private to you.";
"about.developer.header" = "About the developer";
"about.developer.content" = "Hi, I'm Leon.
When I was 8 years old, I went to the Rudolstadt Festival for the first time (at that time it was the \"TFF Rudolstadt\"). Since then, I have been going to the festival again and again and I still find great joy in it. I have now completed my master's degree in computer science and went to Japan with a DAAD scholarship. That means I cannot be at the festival this year, but I still hope the app helps you have a good time in Rudolstadt.

I built this app in my spare time because I wanted a more convenient way to use the festival program. Originally I just wanted to use it myself, but because I was happy with the result, I decided to publish it. Have fun with it!";
